cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

Reasoning: The paper deals with unsupervised feature learning for computer vision tasks, specifically low-level local image descriptors. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of Restricted Boltzmann Machines (RBMs), which are a type of neural network, indicating a possible fit for cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of unsupervised learning methods, which could fit into cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of different descriptors, which could fit into cs.MM (Multimedia).
